p: Online genotyping and subsequent phylogenetic analysis showed that the most frequent clade was sub-subtype A6 (350 sequences; 85.8%). The viral genetic distribution of other sequences was B (29; 7.1%), CRF63_02A1 (14; 3.4%), CRF02_AG (10; 2.5%), G (3; 0.7%), A1 (1; 0.2%), and CRF03_AB (1; 0.2%).
